---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Activity menu - vals.quest">
  <h1>Vals' Activity menu</h1>
  <p>Welcome to a bit of my life! Here I list some activities I like, in case that makes it easier for us to schedule a hang out or find common interests :)</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Conversation</strong>, on whatever you're enthusiastic about, on topics from the <a href="/conversations">conversation menu</a>
      <ul>
        <li>Eg. what's on your mind, personal projects going on, hopes and dreams, becoming oneself, understanding the world</li>
        <li>Phenomenology - what is it like to be you, what's the basis and direction of your life</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Helping out</strong> on whatever work or project you're currently doing, debugging or brainstorming or handiwork (please let me build your ikea furniture).</li>
    <li><strong>Exploring physical space</strong>, urban or rural (ie. walking around, potentially disregarding barriers)
      <ul>
        <li>Hiking and camping and swimming in lakes and rivers</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Sports</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Movement: hiking, climbing, running, cycling, swimming, parapente, skiing, yoga/stretching, acrobranche/via ferrata, dance</li>
        <li>1v1 or team game: badminton, spear fencing, ball games, martial arts eg. Brazilian jiujitsu and wrestling, ping pong</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Social dancing</strong> (lindyhop, rock and roll 6 time, blues, fusion, contact improv)</li>
    <li><strong>Board games</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Social deduction: Blood on the Clocktower, OneNightWerewolves, SecretHitler, ...</li>
        <li>Strategy eg. Dominion, Clank, MTG, Root, ...</li>
        <li>I'll try anything once :D</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Roleplaying</strong> (Shadowrun, Ars Magica, C'thulu, Shadow Musketeers, free form improv, ...) &mdash; <a href="/rpg">see RPG page</a></li>
    <li><strong>Math/logic/coding/physics/philosophy puzzles</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Arts</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Theatre, musicals, films</li>
        <li>Listening to and playing music, singing</li>
        <li>Musical playing and improv, jamming - I play piano, and basic guitar</li>
        <li>Sharing on books, reading literature or poetry for others</li>
        <li>Experimenting with creating stuff</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Video games</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Multiplayer: shooters (CS, Overwatch), RTS (AoM, Rise of Nations, AoE4), platform fighters (Brawlhalla, Rivals of Aether 2), various (7 Days to Die, Minecraft)</li>
        <li>Solo adventures: survival exploration (eg. Subnautica), puzzle games (Understand, Baba is You)</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Writing</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Meditation</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Massages, cuddling</strong></li>
    <li>And I wanna try new things! Share stuff you like or would try :D</li>
  </ul>

  <hr />

  <h2>Less liked activities (things I'm generally not into)</h2>
  <p>I'm able to do any of these, but they're not my favorite for regular activity.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>High effort food</strong> (higher end restaurants, or 30min+/person home cooking) &mdash; I like usual food a lot already</li>
    <li><strong>Loud noise environments</strong> (crowded bars) &mdash; I enjoy dancing during parties - music isn't noise when I'm dancing but is when I'm talking to people</li>
    <li><strong>High risk &amp; high danger things</strong> (eg. high free solo)</li>
    <li><strong>Doing the same activity too much</strong> &mdash; I get satiated. Maybe a few days for skiing or hiking, an hour for puzzles, many hours for cuddling or conversation</li>
  </ul>
</Base>
